I am trying to get a version of cantera installed using Visual C++ 
6.0.  I tried the cvs repository version, and there was an error with 
trying to link clib.dll.  Harry Moffat fixed the cvs repository and I 
tried it again.  The fix seemed to work for the error I was getting, 
but now I get a new error.  So, in order to debug the error, I tried 
downloading the 1.5.4 release assuming it would work.  I 
ran ./configure, built 'all release' in Visual C++, and then 
tried 'make win'.  I get the same error as the cvs repository 
attempt.  The error is shown below.  I get all of these errors 
about 'cannot export such and such: symbol not found'.  Does anyone 
know what is wrong, or how to get it to work in Windows?


c++ -shared -Wl,--enable-auto-image-base build/temp.cygwin-1.5.11-
i686-2.3/src/pycantera.o build/temp.cygwin-1.5.11-i686-
